{{Infobox person | name = Yvette Nicole Brown | image = Yvette Nicole Brown July 2018 (cropped).jpg | caption = Brown at the [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] in July 2018 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1971|08|12}} | birth_place = [[East Cleveland, Ohio]], U.S. | occupation = Actress, voice actress, comedian | years_active = 1992–present | website = {{URL|http://www.yvettenicolebrown.com}} }} '''Yvette Nicole Brown''' (born August 12, 1971) is an American actress, voice actress, and comedian. Brown has appeared in numerous commercials, television shows, and films throughout her career. She starred as [[Shirley Bennett]] on the [[National Broadcasting Company|NBC]] comedy series ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]''. She had a recurring role on the [[Nickelodeon]] sitcom ''[[Drake & Josh]]'' as Helen Dubois, and voiced the character Cookie on the American-Canadian animated series ''[[Pound Puppies (2010 TV series)|Pound Puppies]]''. Brown also starred as Dani in the 2015 version of ''[[The Odd Couple (2015 TV series)|The Odd Couple]]'' on [[CBS]]. Brown has also had small guest roles in television shows such as ''[[That '70s Show]]'', ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'', ''[[Boston Legal]]'', ''[[Chuck (TV series)|Chuck]]'', and ''[[The Soul Man]]''. In addition to television, she has had supporting roles in films such as ''[[(500) Days of Summer]]'', ''[[Tropic Thunder]]'', ''[[Repo Men]]'', and ''[[Percy Jackson: Sea of Monsters]]''. She also voiced "Harper" from the video game ''[[Minecraft: Story Mode]]''. She currently hosts [[Syfy]] [[cosplay]] series ''[[Cosplay Melee]]'' and has been a regular guest on the talk show ''[[Talking Dead]]'' since 2012. ==Early life and education== Brown was born in [[East Cleveland, Ohio]]. She graduated from [[Warrensville Heights High School]] in 1989. Brown studied [[communication studies]] at the [[University of Akron]] and graduated with her Bachelor of Arts in Communication in 1994.{{cite web|url=http://www.uakron.edu/im/online-newsroom/news_details.dot?newsId=1365607&crumbTitle=%27Community%27%20star%20Yvette%20Nicole%20Brown%20to%20be%20honored%20by%20UA|title=''Community'' star Yvette Nicole Brown to be honored by UA|date=31 August 2010|publisher=The University of Akron}}{{cite web|url=http://www.uakron.edu/race/keynote/yvette-nicole-brown.dot|title=Yvette Nicole Brown|publisher=The University of Akron}} She became a sister of the Delta Pi chapter of [[Alpha Kappa Alpha]] as an undergrad at the university. After graduating, Brown took acting classes in [[Hollywood]], [[Los Angeles]].{{cite news|last=Dawidziak|first=Mark|work=[[The Plain Dealer]]|title=Yvette Nicole Brown, an East Cleveland native, enjoys role on TV sitcom ''Community''|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tv/index.ssf/2009/11/yvette_nicole_brown_an_east_cl.html|date=November 13, 2009|accessdate=April 26, 2010}} ==Career== Brown appeared as "Yvette" in the music video "1-4-All-4-1" by the East Coast Family, a [[Michael Bivins]] project, for [[Biv10 Records]].[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xlZv2cpLReM YouTube: East Coast Family 1-4-All-4-1] | Retrieved 11-20-2011 | 2:22 mark Brown said of the experience, "It was a great run, but I guess music was just never meant to be for me."[http://popwatch.ew.com/2009/09/24/community-yvette-nicole-brown-chevy-joel/ EW.com: ''Community'': Get to know Yvette Nicole Brown (and how she got to know Chevy, Joel, Jude, and Gerard)] | 09-24-2009 | Retrieved 11-20-2011 Brown first appeared on commercials before entering television shows and films a few years later.{{cite news|last=Asim|first=Jabari|work=[[The Washington Post]]|title=The 'Trouble' With Black Actresses|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/08/06/AR2006080600806.html|date=August 6, 2006|accessdate=April 26, 2010}} She has since played roles on television shows such as ''[[The War at Home (TV series)|The War At Home]]'', ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'', ''[[That's So Raven]]'', and the US version of ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''. She also had a recurring role as movie theater manager [[Helen Dubois]] in the [[Nickelodeon]] sitcom ''[[Drake & Josh]]''. Brown reprised the role in the season 2 episode of ''[[Victorious]]'' titled "Helen Back Again". She also provided the voice of Cookie on [[Hub Network|The Hub]]'s ''[[Pound Puppies (2010 TV series)|Pound Puppies]]''. In 2009, Brown began starring as [[Shirley Bennett]] on the comedy series ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]''. On September 30, 2014, Brown announced that she would be leaving the show after five seasons in order to take care of her ailing father. In her announcement she said, "My dad needs daily care and he needs me. The idea of being away 16 hours a day for five months, I couldn't do it. It was a difficult decision for me to make, but I had to choose my dad."{{cite web |last=Schneider |first=Michael |url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Yvette-Nicole-Brown-1087724.aspx?rss=news&partnerid=spi&profileid=05 |title=Exclusive: Yvette Nicole Brown Departs ''Community'' |work=[[TV Guide]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=September 30, 2014 |accessdate=October 1, 2014}} She has appeared in television commercials for [[Hamburger Helper]], [[Big Lots]], [[Pine-Sol]], [[Comcast]], [[Aquapod (bottle)|Aquapod]], Shout, Fiber One, [[Yoplait]] Yogurt, [[DiGiorno|DiGiorno Pizza]], [[Dairy Queen]], and [[Time Warner]]. She has appeared on episodes of ''[[The Thrilling Adventure Hour]]'' as "The Troubleshooter" in the ''Sparks Nevada, Marshall On Mars'' series. In 2012, Brown appeared as a celebrity contestant on GSN's version of ''[[Pyramid (game show)|The Pyramid]]'' with her fellow ''Community'' co-star [[Danny Pudi]]. In 2014, it was reported that Brown is set to recur on the [[USA Network]] series ''[[Benched]]''.{{cite web|last1=Dawidziak|first1=Mark|title=Molly Shannon and Yvette Nicole Brown courted for USA Network's 'Benched'|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tv-blog/index.ssf/2014/06/molly_shannon_and_yvette_nicole_brown_courted_for_usa_networks_benched.html|website=cleveland.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}} Shortly after her exit of ''Community'', Brown's role of Dani on the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[The Odd Couple (2015 TV series)|The Odd Couple]]'' was upgraded to series regular.{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2014/10/04/yvette-nicole-brown-the-odd-couple-series-regular-cbs/|title=CBS' Odd Couple Reboot Promotes Yvette Nicole Brown to Series Regular|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|work=TV Line|date=October 4, 2014|accessdate=October 5, 2014}} She has also been a regular guest on AMC's ''[[Talking Dead]]''. She currently hosts [[Syfy]] [[cosplay]] series ''[[Cosplay Melee]]''. In July 2018, Brown temporarily replaced [[Chris Hardwick]] as the host of [[Talking Dead]] and served as moderator for ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]'' and ''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]'' panels at the [[San Diego Comic-Con]]{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/yvette-nicole-brown-replace-chris-hardwick-walking-dead-200343502.html|title=Yvette Nicole Brown to Replace Chris Hardwick as ‘Walking Dead’ Panel Moderator at Comic-Con|publisher=}} during Hardwick’s suspension. ==Filmography== ===Film=== {| class="wikitable sortable" !
